e center of, the natural world. This is a book that reveals science in all its imperfect beauty, crossing the line between observer and observed, scientist and subject, between what is known and what is unknowable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  aCanLit.  aPoetry.  aepistolary poetry.  afiction about science.  amagic realist poetry, Canadian poetry, Canadian literature.  amagic realist poetry.  apoem novel.  apoetry collections that tell stories.  apoetry novel.  aresearch poetry.  ascience poetry.  aweird poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773853734?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773853734423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773853734/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles